f_Z(z)  =  \int_{-\infty}^\infty \mathbf{1}(z-2\theta - x)\mathbf{1}(x)\,dx = \int_0^1 \mathbf{1}(z-2\theta-x)\,dx
2\theta+ 1 <  z < 2\theta + 2
f_Z(z) = \int_{z-2\theta-1}^{1} \,dx = 2 - z+ 2\theta 
2\theta+1 < k < 2\theta+2
P(Z > k) = \int_{k}^{2\theta +2} 2 - z+ 2\theta\,dz = \frac{1}{2}(2-k+2\theta)^2
